Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the noodles.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g} stems lengthways, then cut widthways
into thirds.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @lime{1/2}.

When boiling, add the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%g} and broccoli to the water.

Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop the noodles
sticking together and to keep the veg vibrant.

Meanwhile, boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the @Boiled Water for the Sauce{100%ml} into a #measuring jug{}.

Add the @Ketjap Manis{25%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Peanut Butter{30%g} and
@Sugar for the Sauce{1%tsp}. Stir well.

Pop the #jug{} to one side.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Drain the
@King Prawns{150%g}.

Once hot, add the prawns and stir-fry, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Next, add the @Coleslaw Mix{120%g}. Cook, stirring frequently, until slightly
softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @Red Thai Style Paste{50%g} and the garlic. Cook, stirring, for
~{1%minute} more.

Add the peanut sauce to the frying pan and stir well until combined.

Stir through the cooked noodles and broccoli to coat them in the sauce, then
bring to the boil. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once thickened, remove from the heat.

Add a good squeeze of lime juice and a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Share the prawn noodle stir-fry between your #bowls{}.

Crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} in the unopened @?sachet{} using a #rolling pin{},
then sprinkle over the top to finish.

Serve with any remaining lime cut into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!